A man in his 20s has been arrested on suspicion of murder after a woman was stabbed to death in south London. The woman, believed to be in her 30s, was found with stab wounds on Sudbourne Road in Brixton on Sunday evening. She was pronounced dead at the scene despite the efforts of emergency services. A man was arrested on suspicion of murder following the incident and is in custody at a south London police station. Investigations are continuing at the scene. The pair are thought to have known each other, and the victim’s next of kin have been informed. Formal identification of the woman has not yet been completed. London’s air ambulance attended the incident, and officers from the Metropolitan police homicide and major crime command have been informed.